title: OPEC trims forecast for U.S. oil production growth in 2020
text: The Organization of the Petroleum Exporting Countries on Thursday trimmed its forecast for crude production by the U.S. in 2020. The cartel, in its monthly report, said it expects non-OPEC production to grow by 2.17 million barrels a day next year, down 34,000 barrels a day from its October estimate.
